Package manito.eft.interfaces

Class EPSOriginalTransaction

  • java.lang.Object
    • manito.eft.interfaces.EPSResult
      • manito.eft.interfaces.EPSOriginalTransaction
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Cloneable
    public class EPSOriginalTransaction
extends EPSResult
implements Cloneable
    Entity class for holding details relating to the completion of a previous (successful) transaction.

    Usually needed for reversals.

    See Also:
    Serialized Form

    • Method Detail

      • getAction

        public int getAction()
        Get the Authorisation action requested.

        Supported operations: 

           PAYMENT                  payment by credit, debit or other EFT card
   REFUND                   refund by credit, debit or other EFT card
   REVERSAL                 reversal of previous transaction
   PREVALIDATION            check that a card is valid. operation type can be set in qualifier.
   LOYALTY_AWARD            loyalty award - allocation of points to loyaly card
   PROMOTION_AWARD          promotional award - reward triggered by promotional items, typically
                            a printed voucher
   PAYMENT_WITH_LOYALTY     combined card payment and loyalty award
   ABORT_REQUEST            abort outstanding request
   PREAUTHORISATION         preauthorisation by credit, debit or other EFT card
   FINANCIAL_ADVICE         completion of a preauthorised transaction
   CARD_SWIPE               request for card details
   LOYALTY_SWIPE            loyalty-specific request for card details
   LOYALTY_REDEMPTION       loyalty redemption - payment by loyalty points
   LOYALTY_BALANCE_QUERY    loyalty balance check
   TICKET_REPRINT           reprint last voucher
   CARD_ACTIVATE            activate a gift/loyalty/svc card (put in whitelist)
   CARD_ACTIVATE_REVERSAL   reversal for CARD_ACTIVATE
   CARD_STOP                stop/disable a gift/loyalty/svc card (put in blacklist)
   CARD_STOP_REVERSAL       reversal for CARD_STOP
   SVC_ADD                  add funds into an SVC
   SVC_ADD_REVERSAL         reversal for SVC_ADD
   SVC_DEDUCT               deduct funds from from an SVC
   SVC_DEDUCT_REVERSAL      reversal for SVC_DEDUCT
   BALANCE                  get balance from an SVC/EBT/Credit card account
   AGENT                    online service access
   BILLING                  online bill payment
   E_TOP_UP                 online telephone top-up
        Returns:
        action

      • getActionQualifier

        public int getActionQualifier()
        Get the Qualifier to modify the main action.

        Qualifiers are specific to individual actions.

        Supported action qualifiers: 

           REVERSAL_AUTOMATIC       payment reversal triggered by software e.g. due tio error recovery
   REVERSAL_OPERATOR        payment reversal triggered by operator cancelling the transaction
   AGENT_AUTHORISATION      OnlineAgent request to authorise a payment
   AGENT_COMMIT             OnlineAgent request to commit an authorised payment
   AGENT_REFUND             OnlineAgent request to refund a payment
   AGENT_ENQUIRY            OnlineAgent request to check card validity
   PAYMENT_BY_CARD          Payment by card only - not cheque
   PAYMENT_BY_CHEQUE        Payment by cheque only - not card
   PAYMENT_BY_ANY           Payment by any means available
   REFUND_ITEM_RETURN       Faulty/unwanted item return
   REFUND_PAYMENT_RETURN    Payment return e.g. due to cancellation
   REFUND_CASHBACK          Cashback due to overpayment
   REFUND_PAID_OUT          Paid-out
   LOYALTY_DISCOUNT         Discount due to use of loyalty card
   PROMOTION_DISCOUNT       Discount due to promotional items
   DEFERRED_AWARD           Post-payment/historic award for a sale completed some time before
   COUPON_DISCOUNT          Discount to be applied based on attached coupon
   PROMOTION_DISCOUNT       Discount to be applied based on qualifying items or groups of items
   SVC_PAYMENT              Use card to pay for goods
   SVC_REFUND               Return funds to card due to refunded payment
   SVC_UNLOAD               Withdraw funds from card as cash
   SVC_LOAD                 Add cash onto card (top-up)
   SVC_PRESET_VALUE         Card has a preset value
   SVC_OPEN_VALUE           Card is open value and supports load/unload
   (Card Category)          For BALANCE requests, card category as defined for EPSCard.category
        For PREVALIDATION, the qualifier can be used to specify the intended operation type.
        Returns:
        actionQualifier
